text: Harriet is a rural locality in the North Burnett Region, Queensland, Australia. In the , Harriet had a population of 4 people. == Geography == The locality is bounded to the west by Aranbanga Creek. Harriet Creek rises in Aranbanga in the south and flows through the locality to the north where it becomes a tributary of Aranbanga Creek, a tributary of the Burnett River. The locality presumably takes its name from the creek. == Education == There are no schools in Harriet. The nearest primary and secondary schools are in Gaynah. == References == Category:North Burnett Region Category:Localities in Queensland
